.slides
  %section.title
    %div
      %h1 Red Hat JBoss
      %h3 Enterprise Middleware
      %p
	%small
	  Created by
	  %a{ :href=>"http://hakim.se"}#{site.author}
	  &nbsp;
	  %a{ :href=>"http://twitter.com/jbossdeveloper"}@jbossdeveloper

  %section
    %h2 Status
    %p This is a presentation framework for easily creating beautiful presentations using HTML. You'll need a browser with support for CSS 3D transforms to see it in its full glory.

    %aside.notes
      Oh hey, these are some notes. They'll be hidden in your presentation, but you can see them if you open the speaker notes window (hit 's' on your keyboard).

  / Example of nested vertical slides
  %section
    %section
      %h2 Vertical Slides
      %p
	Slides can be nested inside of other slides,
	try pressing
	= succeed "." do
	  %a.navigate-down{:href => "#"} down
      %a.image.navigate-down{:href => "#"}
	%img{:alt => "Down arrow", :height => "238", :src => "https://s3.amazonaws.com/hakim-static/reveal-js/arrow.png", :width => "178"}/
    %section
      %h2 Basement Level 1
      %p Press down or up to navigate.
    %section
      %h2 Basement Level 2
      %p Cornify
      %a.test{:href => "http://cornify.com"}
	%img{:alt => "Unicorn", :height => "326", :src => "https://s3.amazonaws.com/hakim-static/reveal-js/cornify.gif", :width => "280"}/
    %section
      %h2 Basement Level 3
      %p That's it, time to go back up.
      %a.image{:href => "#/2"}
	%img{:alt => "Up arrow", :height => "238", :src => "https://s3.amazonaws.com/hakim-static/reveal-js/arrow.png", :style => "-webkit-transform: rotate(180deg);", :width => "178"}/
  %section
    %h2 Point of View
    %p
      Press
      %strong ESC
      to enter the slide overview. Hold down alt and click on any element to zoom in on it using
      = succeed "." do
	%a{:href => "http://lab.hakim.se/zoom-js"} zoom.js
      Alt + click anywhere to zoom back out.
  %section
    %h2 slid.es
    %p
      If you don't like writing slides in HTML you can use the online editor
      = succeed "." do
	%a{:href => "http://www.slid.es", :target => "_blank"} slid.es
  %section
    %h2 Works in Mobile Safari
    %p
      Try it out! You can swipe through the slides and pinch your way to the overview.
  %section
    %h2 Marvelous Unordered List
    %ul
      %li No order here
      %li Or here
      %li Or here
      %li Or here
  %section
    %h2 Fantastic Ordered List
    %ol
      %li One is smaller than...
      %li Two is smaller than...
      %li Three!
